the everlasting God who called Abram from the ear of the counties and calls us even today.

38:58.999 --> 39:03.627
So God, thank you for Jesus, the fulfillment of all that you've promised us in your scriptures.

39:03.687 --> 39:06.692
Thank you for Jesus who brings hope to the hopeless.

39:07.373 --> 39:13.042
And so as we respond to you, as we seek to be faithful to steward this movement for the next generation.

39:13.643 --> 39:20.434
Lord, may it never be that we go the way of Hezekiah seeking peace in our day, but instead, like Abram of old, could we plant a tree?

39:20.706 --> 39:27.753
knowing we'll never see it shade, maybe not in our lifetime, but we still planted in hope that one day someone will.

39:27.773 --> 39:29.159
And so we'll thank you in Jesus name.

39:29.902 --> 39:30.002
Amen.

